OL,3,CCustomers describe their 'shock and
OL,4,Cstruggle' over increase in water bills
OL,6,FAntonia Barton, Southern Water's Chief
OL,7,FCustomer Officer, said: "We understand
OL,8,Fan increase in bills is never welcome
OL,9,Fbut our communities have told us that
OL,10,Fwe need to invest more now so we can
OL,11,Fdeliver the real change they expect
OL,12,Fand our environment deserves.
OL,14,F"That's why we must now raise bills,
OL,15,Fwhich have been kept artificially low
OL,16,Ffor too long. Customers will see the
OL,17,Fsharpest rise this summer to allow us
OL,18,Fto frontload investment into major
OL,19,Finfrastructure projects, with future
OL,20,Fannual increases falling for the rest
OL,21,Fof the 2025-30 spending period.
